The paper focuses on deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence, and proposes a novel self-supervised auxiliary task to improve the performance of reinforcement learning algorithms. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on Atari games, which involves image processing and computer vision, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely category. The BipedalWalker domain and the multi-agent Pommerman game involve robotics and game theory, respectively, indicating cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as possible categories.
